article.headline: Nicholls State 38, SE Louisiana 28
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Quarterback Yale Vannoy rushed for 97 yards and had another 122 yards passing to lead Nicholls State to a 38-28 win over Southeastern Louisiana Saturday night. Nicholls (5-3, 4-1 Southland) piled up 392 yards rushing while Southeastern (3-6, 2-4) managed just 83. Joseph Tobias led the Colonels with 107 yards on 13 carries and had two touchdowns -- a 4-yard dash in the first and a 9-yard run to close out scoring in the fourth and seal the win. Lions quarterback Trey Willie was 38-of-57 for 403 yards and three touchdowns on the night and also rushed for a touchdown. Josh Taylor had nine catches for 160 yards and two touchdowns -- a 27-yard catch in the first and a 3 yard grab in the fourth.
